    <h1>Contribute</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="module content">
  <div class="container">
    <p>

    Feeling inspired? Good! As you've noticed, I built the reels so that you can read it one by one. When you have so many ideas thrown at you, it can be overwhelming, but for the most part, just plain annoying. Have an idea of your own? Brilliant! Sign up, pitch your idea, and see what others think. Or build an automaton to do that for you. (Recognize the pictures? They're from a movie called Hugo. It was 3D. Of course there's nothing wrong with that. They make for nice wallpapers. No but genuinely, you should watch it if you haven't seen it yet.)

    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="module parallax parallax-3">
  <div class="container">
    <h1>Recognize</h1>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="module content">
  <div class="container">

    <p>

    The entertainment industry is changing. (This thing called the Internet. Gasp.) The line between creator and audience is becoming less stringent. Some creators cared less what the audience wanted and we were grateful for that. Some industries run on the assumption that they know what we want. Sometimes we have no idea what we want. Sometimes we know exactly what we want. Synopsia is just another way we can talk about what we might, just might, like.

    </p>
  </div>
</section>

